title._content: A Portion of the Squaw Creek National Wildlife Refuge near Mound City, Missouri, in the Northwest Part of the State. The Refuge Is Approximately 6,000 Acres and Is a Stopover for Migratory Shore Birds Heading Up and Down the Mississippi Flyway 02/1975
